 Kei Bridge police arrested a 48-year-old woman for possession of dagga. "The suspect was arrested on Friday, at about 1am, at Deyi Location, Ngquthu Village near Kei Bridge, Butterworth," said police spokesperson, Captain Jackson Manatha. "The dagga has weight of 3,5kg with a street value of R4 000." He said that the suspect was arrested following police intelligence that she was in possession of dagga. The suspect will appear before the Butterworth Magistrate Court on Monday on a charge of possession of dagga. 